summary:
DuckTales Secures A Third Season Ahead Of Second Season Premiere Next Month

  

The Disney Channel have announced that...
caption:
DuckTales Secures A Third Season Ahead Of Second Season Premiere Next Month

The Disney Channel have announced that DuckTales has secured a third season prior to the premiere of season two on 20 October. 

The rebooted 1980s show stars David Tennant in the iconic role of Scrooge McDuck, with Danny Pudi, Ben Schwartz and Bobby Moynihan voicing the mischievous triplets Huey, Dewey and Louie. The cast also includes Kate Micucci as Webby, Toks Olagundoye as Mrs Beakley, Beck Bennett as Launchpad McQuack and Tony Anselmo as Donald Duck.

Several Season Two guest stars have also been revealed including Julie Bowen (“Modern Family”), Edgar Wright (“Baby Driver” director), Jack McBrayer (“30 Rock”), John Hodgman (“Vacationland: True Stories from Painful Beaches”), Jameela Jamil (“The Good Place”), Libe Barer (“Sneaky Pete”) and Lance Reddick (“John Wick”).
The previously announced recurring cast for season two include Paget Brewster (“Criminal Minds”) as Della Duck, Donald Duck’s twin sister and his nephews’ long-lost mother; and Bernardo de Paula (“Rio”) and Arturo del Puerto (“Fear the Walking Dead”) as José de Carioca and Panchito Pistoles of The Three Caballeros.

DuckTales is executive-produced by Emmy Award-nominated Matt Youngberg (“Ben 10: Omniverse”), with Emmy Award-nominated Francisco Angones (Disney XD’s “Wander Over Yonder”) serving as co-producer and story editor, and Sean Jimenez (Disney’s “Gravity Falls”) as art director. The series is a production of Disney Television Animation and carries a TV-Y7 parental guideline.

summary: They had a snafu at fanX on David Tennant’s photo op day. Their equipment server crashed causing many photos to not print (it’s...
caption:
They had a snafu at fanX on David Tennant’s photo op day. Their equipment server crashed causing many photos to not print (it’s no wonder considering they were really rushing people through and I’m really surprised that the interaction we had happened. I love DT so much more than I already did. They worked out a deal where everybody who had photo ops that day would get digital downloads even if they didn’t purchase the digital (those who still wanted their hard copy they’re working out how to get those - I wasn’t affected by the print problem, but benefit from it all the same. And they expanded it to photo-ops on Saturday as well (up to 2PM). I hope that somebody’s learned a lesson about overselling…

Anyway, here are the crystal clear digital versions for prosperity. (cos I’m an over-sharer)

What better way to make the announcement than a video on the Disney Channel Youtube:
